# ci-decision-golden.json.meta — provenance sidecar for ci-decision-golden.json (#399 W1d, R4).
#
# Captures decision-level parity between the PRE-#399 ci_is_green (byte-identical
# gh-argv passthrough where the caller's `--json state -q '[.[].state]'` returned a
# per-check state array and the caller applied `length>0 and all(.=="SUCCESS")`
# on that array) and the POST-#399 ci_is_green (which captures the new
# `chp_ci_status`'s single normalized token `green|pending|failed|none` and
# tests `[[ "$token" == "green" ]]`).
#
# Rows are the six TC-DSAP-004 fixture classes PLUS the four gh rc-quirk cases
# R2 pins:
#
#   all_success_one, all_success_many        — ≥1 SUCCESS, no other state → green (rc 0)
#   mixed_pending                            — SUCCESS + PENDING → pending (rc 1)
#   mixed_failure                            — SUCCESS + FAILURE → failed (rc 1)
#   skipped_success                          — SKIPPED + SUCCESS → pending (rc 1, SKIPPED != SUCCESS)
#   empty_array                              — [] → none (rc 1)
#   transport_error                          — gh rc≠0 + empty stdout → leaf rc≠0, ci_is_green rc 1
#   failure_and_skipped                      — rule 2 beats rule 3 (FAILURE + SKIPPED → failed)
#   cancelled_and_pending                    — CANCELLED terminal → failed (rule 2)
#   in_progress_only                         — IN_PROGRESS only → pending (rule 3)
#   rc_nonzero_valid_json_success            — gh rc-quirk: rc≠0 with parseable JSON → derive token from stdout
#   rc_nonzero_garbage_stdout                — genuine transport failure: rc≠0 + non-JSON → leaf rc≠0
#
# For every row, `old_ci_is_green_rc == new_ci_is_green_rc` — this file IS the
# decision-parity contract R4 pins. The rc-quirk cases were not exercised by
# the pre-#399 caller because the OLD leaf's argv `--json state -q '[.[].state]'`
# would emit `[]` on stdout for the "failing checks" rc-quirk (gh's -q filter
# still runs) — for those pre-existing quirk shapes both OLD and NEW ended in
# rc 1 anyway (empty state array is not `all=="SUCCESS"`); the NEW leaf makes
# the distinction between "rc-quirk with data" and "genuine transport failure"
# via the R2 stdout-parseable-JSON test.
#
# Regenerate (only if the OLD ci_is_green semantics are ever in dispute):
# checkout the commit immediately before #399's leaf rewrite, source
# lib-dispatch.sh under the fixture harness in
# tests/unit/test-w1d-ci-status-mergeable-parity.sh, feed each row's
# `gh_stdout` / `gh_rc` through a stub `chp_ci_status`, and record the
# resulting ci_is_green rc.
